IRS990.Desc: SKILLED NURSING AND LONG-TERM REHABILITATION SERVICES PROVIDED SERVICE TO 45 PATIENTS FOR A TOTAL OF 16,424 PATIENT DAYS. PATIENTS INCLUDED THE MEDICALLY NEEDY AND PHYSICALLY IMPAIRED SUPPORTED BY MEDICAID, MEDICARE, VETERANS ADMINISTRATION, STATE LABOR AND INDUSTRY, PRIVATE INSURERS, AS WELL AS CHARITABLE RESOURCES. SKILLED NURSING RESIDENTS AGE RANGE FROM 20 TO OVER 100. THE FACILITY OFFERS A SPECIALIZED ALZHEIMER'S LIVING CENTER THAT IS SAFE AND SECURE, AND PROMOTES INDEPENDENCE IN A DIGNIFIED WAY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: RESIDENT TRUST ACCOUNTS ARE HELD BY THE ORGANIZATION.

THE ORGANIZATION ADOPTED THE PROVISIONS OF ASC 740-10, INCOME TAXES, RELATING TO ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS ON APRIL 1, 2009, WHICH HAD NO FINANCIAL STATEMENT IMPACT TO THE ORGANIZATION. THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES THE TAX BENEFIT FROM UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THE TAX POSITIONS WILL BE SUSTAINED ON EXAMINATION BY THE TAX AUTHORITIES, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. THE TAX BENEFIT IS MEASURED BASED ON THE LARGEST BENEFIT THAT HAS A GREATER THAN 50% LIKELIHOOD OF BEING REALIZED UPON ULTIMATE SETTLEMENT. THE ORGANIZATION IS SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY U.S. FEDERAL (OR STATE AND LOCAL) INCOME TAX AUTHORITIES FOR THREE YEARS FROM THE FILING OF A TAX RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SEA MAR SKILLED NURSING HAS A MANAGEMENT AGREEMENT WITH A RELATED ENTITY, SEA MAR COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER (CHC) TO OPERATE, ADMINISTER, AND MANAGE THE FACILITY. THIS AGREEMENT GIVES CHC THE POWER TO HIRE, PROMOTE, DISCHARGE AND SUPERVISE THE WORK OF THE FACILITY ADMINISTRATOR AND ALL OTHER STAFF; OVERSEE THE ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT; HANDLE COMMUNICATIONS FROM PATIENTS, FAMILIES OF PATIENTS, AND OTHER USERS OF THE FACILITY; PURCHASE OPERATING EQUIPMENT AND SUPPLIES. CHC DONATES THESE SERVICES TO SKILLED NURSING. FOR THE FISCAL YEAR ENDING MARCH 31, 2018 THE VALUE OF SERVICES PROVIDED WAS $108,000. CHC IS ALSO THE COMMON PAYMASTER FOR SKILLED NURSING'S EMPLOYEES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A) DEFINITION - A BOARD MEMBER SHALL BE CONSIDERED TO HAVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST WHEN HE/SHE (OR SOMEONE IN THAT BOARD MEMBER'S OWN IMMEDIATE FAMILY) COULD BE FINANCIALLY AFFECTED BY A RECOMMENDATION OR DECISION OF THE BOARD. (THIS EXCLUDES UTILIZATION OF SEA MAR SERVICES AND POLICIES REGARDING SERVICES PROVIDED BY SEA MAR.) ANY MEMBER SERVING ON ANOTHER DECISION-MAKING BODY THAT WOULD BE DIRECTLY AFFECTED BY AN ACTION OF THE BOARD WOULD ALSO HAVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST. NO BOARD MEMBER MAY PARTICIPATE IN THE SELECTION, AWARD, OR ADMINISTRATION OF A CONTRACT SUPPORTED BY FEDERAL FUNDS IF A REAL OR APPARENT CONFLICT OF INTEREST WOULD BE INVOLVED. SUCH A CONFLICT WOULD ARISE WITH A BOARD MEMBER OR ANY OF HIS OR HER IMMEDIATE FAMILY, HIS OR HER PARTNER, OR AN ORGANIZATION WHICH EMPLOYEES OR IS ABOUT TO EMPLOY ANY OF THE PARTIES INDICATED HEREIN, HAS A FINANCIAL OR OTHER INTEREST IN THE FIRM SELECTED FOR AN AWARD. THE BOARD MEMBERS SHALL NEITHER SOLICIT NOR ACCEPT GRATUITIES, FAVORS, OR ANYTHING OF MONETARY VALUE FROM CONTRACTORS OF THE CORPORATION OR PARTIES TO AGREEMENTS WITHIN THE CORPORATION. B) DETERMINATION OF CONFLICT OF INTEREST - ANY BOARD MEMBER WHO FEELS THAT HE/SHE HAS A POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST REGARDING BUSINESS BEFORE THE BOARD SHOULD DECLARE THAT HE/SHE HAS A CONFLICT. ANY MEMBER MAY CHALLENGE ANOTHER MEMBER IF HE/SHE FEELS THAT A CONFLICT EXISTS AND HAS NOT BEEN DECLARED. IF THERE IS ANY QUESTION AS TO WHETHER A CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTS, THE MATTER SHALL BE DETERMINED BY A MAJORITY VOTE OF THE BOARD OR ITS COMMITTEES. C) ABSTENTION FOR BUSINESS AT HAND - ANY MEMBER DETERMINED TO HAVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST SHALL BE EXCLUDED FROM VOTING ON THE MATTER AT HAND. D) VIOLATIONS - ANY BOARD MEMBER WHO KNOWINGLY VIOLATES THE PROVISIONS OF THIS SECTION 9 SHALL BE SUBJECT TO ACTION BY THE BOARD, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO CENSURE, REMOVAL FROM THE BOARD PURSUANT TO SECTION 19, OR SUCH OTHER ACTION AS THE BOARD MAY DEEM APPROPRIATE.
